** Phased Array Technician **

IRISNDT

Full-time, Brisbane

** Exciting Opportunities Await You! **

We are looking for applications from Phased Array Technicians. IRISNDT are
world leaders in asset integrity services, we are eagerly seeking applications
from passionate and qualified individuals to join our esteemed teams. We have
branches nationally across Perth, Melbourne, Newcastle, Brisbane, and
Gladstone, offering you a diverse range of opportunities.

We cover all areas, including Green Energy, Oil and Gas, Mining, and Power
Generation. Whatever your passion or expertise, we have opportunities that
align with your career goals.

** Key Responsibilities: **

  * Conduct cutting-edge NDT and inspection work that pushes the boundaries of technological advancement. 
  * Utilize your expertise to prepare and compile comprehensive reports that make a real impact. 
  * Showcase your technical prowess through equipment maintenance and calibration. 
  * Embrace our unwavering commitment to safety, ensuring a secure work environment for all. 
  * Thrive in an environment that occasionally requires you to work away from home, adding an adventurous touch to your career. 

Anyone with a keen eye for detail and a passion for excellence will find a
place to shine within our organisation.

** Key Attributes: **

  * Bring your honesty, integrity, and reliability to the forefront of our operations. 
  * Display versatility by working autonomously and harmoniously within a diverse team environment. 
  * Leverage your experience in working with a variety of international standards and customer specifications. 
  * Demonstrate proficiency in reading and understanding technical drawings. 
  * Showcase your expertise in MS Office programs. 

With our flexible working options, you can find a work-life balance that suits
your needs. We understand the importance of your personal life and strive to
provide schedules that allow you to thrive both on and off the job.

** About Us: **

We take pride in being a privately-owned company with a global presence. Our
asset integrity services have made us a trusted name in Canada, the USA, the
United Kingdom, and Australia (Brisbane, Newcastle, Sydney, Melbourne &
Perth). With over 1600 staff globally, we specialize in NDT and inspection
services, asset integrity & materials engineering, failure analysis, rope
access, and software services. Joining our team means being part of a growing
organization that is in high demand for its exceptional services.

